---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../../components/HeroSection.astro';
import SignupForm from '../../components/SignupForm.astro';
import { donateUrl } from '../../data/navigation';
---

<PageLayout title="Transportation | Fatmata Barrie" description="Fatmata Barrie's platform on transit, commuting, bike infrastructure, and transportation equity in Montgomery County.">

  <HeroSection title="Transportation" subtitle="Montgomery County residents deserve better options — to commute, get around, and get on with their lives." />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container priority-layout">

      <div class="priority-body">

        <p class="priority-intro">
          The Washington DC Metro area has some of the worst traffic in the country — taking the average resident over an hour to commute every day. Fatmata understands that too many residents are spending too much time in traffic. Our public transportation also does not meet the needs of all county residents by providing reliable transportation throughout the county. Fatmata will fight for a transportation system that works for everyone.
        </p>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Improve WMATA Access and Complete the Purple Line</h2>
          <p>Fatmata will work with regional leaders to improve WMATA access and affordability, as well as get a real timeline on the completion of the Purple Line — providing more consistency in alternatives to driving for Montgomery County commuters and residents.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Expand Bike Lanes and Protections for Cyclists</h2>
          <p>Fatmata will work to increase bike lanes across the county so more people can bike to and from work as well as for leisure. She will also fight to create more protections for bikers to decrease the danger on major roads — making cycling a safe, viable option for more county residents.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Expand RideOn Services</h2>
          <p>Fatmata will fight to expand RideOn services to more areas of the county and with more frequency. More consistency in public transportation grows ridership, reduces traffic, and makes for safer roads — giving every resident a reliable way to get where they need to go.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Why This Matters for Montgomery County</h2>
          <p>Transportation is about more than getting from Point A to Point B. It is about access to opportunity. When residents can get to work reliably, when students can get to school safely, when people of all abilities can move freely through their community, the whole county is stronger. Transportation equity is economic equity — and Fatmata will treat it that way.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-closing">
          <p>Whether you drive, take the bus, ride a bike, or walk — your commute matters. Fatmata will fight to build a transportation system that treats every resident's time and safety as the priority they deserve to be.</p>
          <div class="priority-cta-buttons">
            <a href={donateUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-accent">Donate to the Campaign</a>
            <a href="/volunteer" class="btn btn-primary">Get Involved</a>
            <a href="/priorities" class="btn btn-outline">Back to All Priorities</a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside class="priority-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <h3>Key Actions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Improve WMATA access and get a real timeline on Purple Line completion</li>
            <li>Increase bike lanes and protections for cyclists countywide</li>
            <li>Expand RideOn services to more areas and with more frequency</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-card sidebar-nav">
          <h3>Other Priorities</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/priorities/affordability">Affordability &amp; Housing</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/business">Business &amp; Economy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/climate">Climate Justice</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/democracy">Defending Democracy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/education">Education</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/health">Health</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/safety">Safer Communities</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/seniors">Seniors &amp; Aging</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/womens-health">Women's Health</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </section>

  <SignupForm />

</PageLayout>

<style>
  .priority-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .priority-intro {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-light);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .priority-section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

  .priority-section h2 { font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem); color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  .priority-section p { color: var(--text); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  .priority-closing {
    background: var(--cream);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .priority-closing p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  .priority-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .btn-outline {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.5rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--primary);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--primary);
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    transition: all var(--transition);
  }

  .btn-outline:hover { background: var(--primary); color: var(--white); }

  .priority-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; position: sticky; top: 90px; }

  .sidebar-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .sidebar-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sidebar-card ul { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }

  .sidebar-card ul li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .sidebar-card ul li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.5rem;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
  }

  .sidebar-nav ul li::before { background: var(--teal); }
  .sidebar-nav ul li a { color: var(--primary); font-size: 0.9rem; transition: color var(--transition); }
  .sidebar-nav ul li a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .priority-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .priority-sidebar { position: static; }
    .priority-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; }
    .priority-cta-buttons .btn { text-align: center; }
  }
</style>
